 MiB: Jawad Mian, Stray Reflections https://ritholtz.com/2023/07/mib-jawad-mian/Barry Ritholtz Sat, 22 Jul 2023 13:00:46 +0000 Macro/EconMiB https://ritholtz.com/?p=317016 <p> This week, we speak with Jawad S. Mian, who is the founder and managing editor at Stray Reflections, an independent global macro research and trading advisory firm with a focus on major investment themes. His clients include some of the world&#39;s largest hedge funds, family offices, and institutional investors. Mian studied finance and economics…</p><p><a class="button" href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/07/mib-jawad-mian/">阅读更多<i class="icon ion-arrow-right-c"></i></a></p><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/07/mib-jawad-mian/">MiB: Jawad Mian, Stray Reflections</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ritholtz.com">The Big Picture</a> .</p> ; <p><iframe style="width: 100%; max-width: 660px; overflow: hidden; border-radius: 10px;" src="https://embed.podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/jawad-s-mian-on-global-investment-research/id730188152?i=1000621899002" height="175" frameborder="0" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation"></iframe></p><p></p><p> This week, we speak with Jawad S. Mian, who is the founder and managing editor at <a href="https://stray-reflections.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stray Reflections</a> , an independent global macro research and trading advisory firm with a focus on major investment themes. His clients include some of the world&#39;s largest hedge funds, family offices, and institutional investors. Mian studied finance and economics at the University of Western Ontario and is a CFA and CMT charter holder.</p><p> We discuss what makes a secular bull market so strong, pervasive, long-lasting, and resilient. Rather than focusing on future predictions, he focuses on trying to fully understand what is going on right now, a task that is much harder than it sounds.</p><p> Mian explains why, despite all the predictions to the contrary, we have not fallen into a recession. Rate sensitivity in the US economy is historically low. Post-GFC, the “beautiful de-leveraging” (as Ray Dalio of Bridgewater termed it) took time, but post-pandemic, the economic recovery was much faster and stronger. Fiscal stimulus boost to incomes and a further drop in costs led the Household debt service to disposable income ratio to its lowest point, below the 1980 levels, when the data series first began.</p><p> A list of his favorite books <a href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/07/mib-jawad-mian/#more-317016" target="_blank" rel="noopener">is here</a> ; A transcript of our conversation is <a href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/07/transcript-jawad-mian/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">available here</a> Tuesday.</p><p>您可以在<a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/masters-in-business/id730188152" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apple Podcasts</a> 、 <a href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/3s05WHoHBr6OKXi1URzhxf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Spotify</a> 、 <a href="https://www.stitcher.com/show/masters-in-business/episode/jawad-s-mian-on-global-investment-research-305461246" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stitcher</a> 、 <a href="https://podcasts.google.com/feed/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cub21ueWNvbnRlbnQuY29tL2QvcGxheWxpc3QvZTczYzk5OGUtNmU2MC00MzJmLTg2MTAtYWUyMTAxNDBjNWIxLzRlNGNkOTEwLTQwYTEtNDYxOS1hNWYzLWFlMmIwMDEyZmZmZi81ODczYTNjYi0yOThmLTQwYmMtYjcxZi1hZTJiMDAxMzAwMGQvcG9kY2FzdC5yc3M" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google</a> 、 <a href="https://youtu.be/IEFPCCLHL_k" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube</a>和<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/audio/2023-07-21/jawad-s-mian-on-global-investment-research-podcast" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bloomberg</a>上流式传输和下载我们的完整对话，包括任何播客附加内容。您可以<a class="gtrackexternal" href="https://plnk.to/MIB?to=page">在此处找到</a>您最喜欢的播客主机上的所有早期播客。</p><p> Be sure to check out our <a href="https://ritholtz.com/category/podcast/mib/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-web-url="http://www.bloombergview.com/topics/masters-in-business">Masters in Business</a> next week with Liz Hoffman, Liz Hoffman, the Business and Finance Editor at Semafor. Previously, she was a senior reporter at Wall Street Journal covering finance, investment banking and M&amp;A. Following a string of front-page articles on Goldman Sachs push into Main St, and the travails of the world&#39;s largest VC, she moved to Semafor. Her new book is <a href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0593239016/thebigpictu09-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Crash Landing: The Inside Story of How the World&#39;s Biggest Companies Survived an Economy on the Brink</em></a> .</p><p></p><p><span id="more-317016"></span></p><p></p><h3> Jawad Mian Favorite Books</h3><p> <strong><a href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0060652934/thebigpictu09-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Screwtape Letters</a></strong> by CS Lewis<br /> <a href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0060652934/thebigpictu09-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-316895" src="https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/screwtape.jpg" alt="" width="250" height="376" srcset="https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/screwtape.jpg 332w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/screwtape-200x300.jpg 200w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/screwtape-250x376.jpg 250w" sizes="(max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px" /></a></p><p> <strong><a href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0062315005/thebigpictu09-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Alchemist, 25th Anniversary: A Fable About Following Your Dream</a></strong> by Paulo Coelho<br /> <a href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0062315005/thebigpictu09-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-316896" src="https://ritholtz.c